WEBVTT


00:00:14.938 --> 00:00:15.980
Mibu!

00:00:16.688 --> 00:00:17.521
Here…

00:00:19.896 --> 00:00:22.730
Someone left another
weird bouquet this year.

00:00:24.271 --> 00:00:26.230
It's just a misdirected grudge.

00:00:27.063 --> 00:00:28.146
Don't worry about it.

00:00:29.855 --> 00:00:30.730
Okay.

00:00:34.438 --> 00:00:37.521
It smells so clean and nice.

00:00:38.896 --> 00:00:40.980
Thanks to you, Mr. Koyama,

00:00:41.063 --> 00:00:43.896
I can live comfortably in a hotel.

00:00:43.980 --> 00:00:45.105
You're a big help.

00:00:45.188 --> 00:00:47.980
I owe you a lot, Mr. Kyogoku.

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:50.938
It's no trouble at all

00:00:51.438 --> 00:00:53.063
to prepare a room under my name.

00:01:02.855 --> 00:01:04.730
People in our line of work

00:01:04.813 --> 00:01:08.146
can't stay in hotels that require us
to write down our real names.

00:01:08.938 --> 00:01:11.896
If we use a fake name,
we'll get locked up for fraud.

00:01:11.980 --> 00:01:16.521
So we can only stay in love hotels,
even if we have money.

00:01:19.396 --> 00:01:23.063
I took care of that thing
you asked me to do.

00:01:23.146 --> 00:01:23.980
Huh?

00:01:24.063 --> 00:01:26.021
The parent problem.

00:01:26.605 --> 00:01:32.188
He ruined a major cash cow and star,
Shizuku Pien, for just three million.

00:01:32.271 --> 00:01:34.063
I had to settle the score.

00:01:34.146 --> 00:01:36.771
Her parent who sued us…

00:01:37.480 --> 00:01:40.646
I had his crotch burned off,
and he was turned into a eunuch.

00:01:41.438 --> 00:01:46.146
I saw a photo of him after the punishment.
He'll never be able to use it again.

00:01:47.396 --> 00:01:52.646
He'll have to use a catheter
for the rest of his life.

00:01:53.146 --> 00:01:55.021
What? He's still alive?

00:01:58.021 --> 00:01:58.855
Huh?

00:01:58.938 --> 00:02:01.855
What if he talks?
Are you sure it'll be okay?

00:02:09.146 --> 00:02:10.271
What?

00:02:11.063 --> 00:02:12.271
You want me to kill him?

00:02:13.896 --> 00:02:14.730
Oh, no.

00:02:19.146 --> 00:02:21.271
I'm expressing that I'm thirsty.

00:02:22.188 --> 00:02:23.521
Didn't you notice?

00:02:25.688 --> 00:02:27.230
Sorry. I'll get it right away.

00:02:39.938 --> 00:02:43.021
Don't worry about him talking.

00:02:43.105 --> 00:02:45.813
They'll never be able
to trace it back to you.

00:02:46.313 --> 00:02:47.480
I see.

00:02:47.980 --> 00:02:49.105
Here you go.

00:02:50.021 --> 00:02:53.688
Oh, right. I have a favor to ask.

00:02:53.771 --> 00:02:56.855
Can you lend me one
of your popular actresses for a day?

00:02:56.938 --> 00:02:59.855
Yes. I'll call our most popular actress
here right away.

00:02:59.938 --> 00:03:00.896
That's not it.

00:03:00.980 --> 00:03:01.813
Yes?

00:03:02.396 --> 00:03:05.646
I want an amateur tape of a cocky CEO,
who's married with kids,

00:03:05.730 --> 00:03:07.896
hooking up with a popular actress.

00:03:07.980 --> 00:03:10.105
We'll secretly film them
and blackmail him.

00:03:10.980 --> 00:03:13.188
The end goal is to take over his company.

00:03:13.271 --> 00:03:14.355
For that,

00:03:14.438 --> 00:03:17.855
I'll get Attorney Kujo on our side
and have him work like a pigeon.

00:03:24.105 --> 00:03:26.855
The higher the mountain,
the deeper the valley.

00:03:29.855 --> 00:03:32.021
I'll show him
what rock bottom really means.

00:03:39.855 --> 00:03:42.355
Attorney Karasuma, are you feeling unwell?

00:03:42.855 --> 00:03:44.938
It's not my body. It's my heart.

00:03:45.021 --> 00:03:46.188
Your heart?

00:03:47.271 --> 00:03:49.480
Any case involving Mibu
leads to that person.

00:03:50.855 --> 00:03:52.521
Who do you mean by "that person"?

00:03:53.063 --> 00:03:54.938
You know who I'm talking about.

00:03:55.521 --> 00:03:56.563
Kyogoku…

00:03:57.063 --> 00:03:57.938
Go in.

00:04:05.688 --> 00:04:08.188
Thank you, Attorney Kujo.

00:04:08.688 --> 00:04:13.313
Do you remember?
I met you two before at Kiko Nursing Home.

00:04:13.396 --> 00:04:14.521
Of course.

00:04:14.605 --> 00:04:18.188
At the time, I never imagined
that you were acquainted with Mibu.

00:04:18.271 --> 00:04:22.146
I was ordered by Mibu
to keep an eye on the CEO, Mr. Sugawara.

00:04:24.021 --> 00:04:26.146
We're brothers who shared a cup.

00:04:26.230 --> 00:04:28.105
I'll kill you if you betray me.

00:04:28.605 --> 00:04:31.271
I was found out and beaten half to death.

00:04:32.146 --> 00:04:34.813
After all that,
I'm surprised you still work for Mibu.

00:04:36.521 --> 00:04:38.521
He's the one who saved my life.

00:04:41.605 --> 00:04:42.730
Mr. Kuga,

00:04:43.230 --> 00:04:46.813
you were arrested on suspicion
of violating the Employment Security Act.

00:04:47.313 --> 00:04:50.230
You were suspected
of introducing girls to an escort agency

00:04:50.313 --> 00:04:52.605
for the purpose
of making them do sex work.

00:04:52.688 --> 00:04:53.855
Sir,

00:04:54.521 --> 00:04:56.063
these are separate charges.

00:04:57.146 --> 00:04:59.396
Why do you consider it a separate arrest?

00:05:00.646 --> 00:05:05.021
Last week, a driver named Tonohata,
who works for our escort agency,

00:05:05.105 --> 00:05:07.480
was kidnapped and assaulted.

00:05:07.980 --> 00:05:10.896
I was interrogated as a suspect.

00:05:10.980 --> 00:05:13.105
Why were you suspected?

00:05:13.938 --> 00:05:17.313
Tonohata set fire to my car.

00:05:17.813 --> 00:05:20.396
He was caught
on the security camera and arrested.

00:05:20.480 --> 00:05:23.771
It seems that he was pushed
by the police to cooperate.

00:05:24.855 --> 00:05:27.980
Sir, am I going to be taken away?

00:05:28.771 --> 00:05:31.688
I don't know what Tonohata
has fessed up to and how much,

00:05:31.771 --> 00:05:33.813
so I can't give a definitive answer yet.

00:05:35.521 --> 00:05:37.480
Did you lay a hand on Tonohata?

00:05:37.563 --> 00:05:39.688
No, not at all.

00:05:39.771 --> 00:05:42.355
I was in Fukuoka that day.

00:05:43.230 --> 00:05:44.730
I see. Understood.

00:05:45.230 --> 00:05:48.313
If there's no other evidence,
don't say anything unnecessary.

00:05:48.396 --> 00:05:49.980
Remain silent.

00:05:51.396 --> 00:05:53.313
Would I be able to remain silent?

00:05:53.813 --> 00:05:56.980
Arashiyama, the lead detective
from the Organized Crime Division,

00:05:57.063 --> 00:05:58.521
really gets on my nerves.

00:05:58.605 --> 00:05:59.813
Detective Arashiyama?

00:05:59.896 --> 00:06:00.813
Yes.

00:06:00.896 --> 00:06:06.105
He's really aggressive towards me,
so I feel like I might talk back to him.

00:06:06.188 --> 00:06:08.771
Do you know why
he's being aggressive with you?

00:06:11.938 --> 00:06:13.813
Arashiyama's daughter

00:06:15.396 --> 00:06:16.730
was murdered.

00:06:17.813 --> 00:06:20.855
Everyone, halt!

00:06:22.021 --> 00:06:23.396
Line up!

00:06:25.355 --> 00:06:26.771
The one who killed her…

00:06:27.271 --> 00:06:28.855
Face left!

00:06:29.480 --> 00:06:31.688
…was a guy named Yuto Inukai.

00:06:32.230 --> 00:06:34.688
He was a friend from my hometown.

00:06:42.271 --> 00:06:49.230
That's why Arashiyama resents me and Mibu.

00:06:52.688 --> 00:06:53.896
Attorney Karasuma.

00:06:53.980 --> 00:06:55.396
HONJO POLICE STATION

00:06:55.480 --> 00:06:58.771
Have you tried the takoyaki
advertised as "Japan's top takoyaki"?

00:06:58.855 --> 00:06:59.688
What?

00:06:59.771 --> 00:07:00.813
Takoyaki.

00:07:00.896 --> 00:07:03.355
This is not the time
to be talking about that.

00:07:03.438 --> 00:07:04.771
Why are you so carefree?

00:07:04.855 --> 00:07:07.105
Let's buy it today and see if it's true.

00:07:07.188 --> 00:07:08.646
With lots of mayonnaise.

00:07:08.730 --> 00:07:10.021
Attorney Kujo.

00:07:11.980 --> 00:07:15.938
Why have you become a lapdog
for the yakuza and gangs? Is it for money?

00:07:17.146 --> 00:07:19.980
What is this all of a sudden?
You're being rude.

00:07:20.063 --> 00:07:24.938
You're the son of the famous prosecutor,
Yukisada Kurama.

00:07:25.021 --> 00:07:28.355
And your older brother,
Kuroudo Kurama, is also a prosecutor.

00:07:29.105 --> 00:07:32.563
Your brother is on the career track,
so don't get in his way.

00:07:33.813 --> 00:07:35.563
That's none of your business.

00:07:36.146 --> 00:07:38.771
Between them and me,
we're all different individuals.

00:07:38.855 --> 00:07:40.605
You shouldn't lump us together.

00:07:41.605 --> 00:07:44.313
And I've already cut ties with my family.

00:07:44.396 --> 00:07:46.313
That's not how society sees it.

00:07:47.855 --> 00:07:50.521
Why should I care
about what society thinks?

00:07:51.146 --> 00:07:52.396
Excuse me.

00:07:53.480 --> 00:07:55.521
Are you Attorney Karasuma?

00:07:56.021 --> 00:07:56.896
Yes.

00:07:56.980 --> 00:08:00.355
Do you do it for money too?
But you're still young.

00:08:00.438 --> 00:08:03.438
-Did you become an attorney to do this?
-No, I didn't.

00:08:56.605 --> 00:09:00.480
Is it true that you cut ties
with your brother, Prosecutor Kurama?

00:09:00.563 --> 00:09:03.313
Yes, it's true.

00:09:03.980 --> 00:09:05.688
Why did you do that?

00:09:18.313 --> 00:09:20.188
Who was that just now?

00:09:23.355 --> 00:09:25.730
Detective Arashiyama
of the Organized Crime Division.

00:09:25.813 --> 00:09:27.980
Oh, that's him.

00:09:28.938 --> 00:09:30.855
I don't like the way detectives think.

00:09:31.896 --> 00:09:34.313
Detectives think in binary terms.

00:09:35.271 --> 00:09:38.146
They only see people
as suspects or collaborators.

00:09:38.230 --> 00:09:40.646
We can never have a decent conversation.

00:09:40.730 --> 00:09:43.771
But his daughter was murdered, right?

00:09:44.396 --> 00:09:47.646
Do you know about that case,
Attorney Kujo?

00:09:52.313 --> 00:09:53.813
It was ten years ago.

00:09:55.605 --> 00:09:58.896
A woman's body was found on the riverbank.

00:10:01.230 --> 00:10:04.105
The body was
that of 20-year-old Manami Ogawa,

00:10:04.605 --> 00:10:06.480
Detective Arashiyama's daughter.

00:10:06.563 --> 00:10:09.063
Her parents divorced,
so her surname was different.

00:10:10.188 --> 00:10:12.938
Several minors were promptly arrested

00:10:13.021 --> 00:10:17.105
after multiple bodily fluids, believed
to belong to the perpetrators, were found.

00:10:17.188 --> 00:10:19.896
Manami Ogawa was attacked from behind
on her way home,

00:10:19.980 --> 00:10:21.480
and her valuables were stolen.

00:10:21.563 --> 00:10:23.271
Then she was assaulted.

00:10:24.105 --> 00:10:27.230
She screamed,
so they strangled her to death.

00:10:28.396 --> 00:10:30.021
-Second dish.
-Third dish coming.

00:10:30.105 --> 00:10:31.771
-First dish.
-Third dish.

00:10:31.855 --> 00:10:34.396
The one who actually killed her,
Yuto Inukai,

00:10:34.480 --> 00:10:37.563
was sentenced to an indeterminate term
of ten to fifteen years

00:10:37.646 --> 00:10:39.438
and is still serving his time.

00:10:40.230 --> 00:10:42.313
The two accomplices have been released

00:10:42.396 --> 00:10:44.063
and are in social rehabilitation.

00:10:47.646 --> 00:10:50.688
Detective Arashiyama,
is Mr. Kuga really guilty?

00:10:50.771 --> 00:10:52.271
Of course he's guilty.

00:10:52.355 --> 00:10:53.355
But he has an alibi.

00:10:53.438 --> 00:10:55.480
He was in Fukuoka that day. And--

00:10:55.563 --> 00:10:56.646
Fukami,

00:10:57.230 --> 00:11:01.313
it's hard to see through
a person's true nature

00:11:01.396 --> 00:11:02.855
if you're spaced out.

00:11:02.938 --> 00:11:04.646
A person's true nature?

00:11:04.730 --> 00:11:09.230
The face they show in public
and to family. And their true face.

00:11:10.313 --> 00:11:14.230
Only the person themselves and those
who share their sins know their true face.

00:11:16.896 --> 00:11:21.313
Don't just study the perpetrator. Look at
the victim's personality and home life.

00:11:21.396 --> 00:11:24.230
Find out why
they were involved in the crime.

00:11:24.313 --> 00:11:26.230
It's the golden rule of investigation.

00:11:27.688 --> 00:11:29.605
-Yes.
-Okay. Good job today.

00:11:30.438 --> 00:11:31.855
Where are you going?

00:11:31.938 --> 00:11:33.855
I have something to do at home.

00:11:35.355 --> 00:11:38.188
I understand the outline of the case.

00:11:38.271 --> 00:11:40.605
But why does
Detective Arashiyama resent Mibu

00:11:40.688 --> 00:11:43.521
for being senior to Inukai,
the main perpetrator?

00:11:44.521 --> 00:11:47.271
This is just my guess, but…

00:11:48.438 --> 00:11:52.021
Detective Arashiyama knows
that Mr. Kyogoku is above Mibu.

00:11:54.146 --> 00:11:58.355
See? I told you
not to get involved with Mr. Kyogoku.

00:11:59.438 --> 00:12:02.813
This means they might've been involved
in the murder case, right?

00:12:03.355 --> 00:12:06.813
Get involved with people like that,
and you'll really lose your badge.

00:12:06.896 --> 00:12:09.896
Like I said, this is just my guess.

00:12:13.730 --> 00:12:14.813
Then,

00:12:15.646 --> 00:12:19.230
are you saying that
Detective Arashiyama's case isn't over?

00:12:22.813 --> 00:12:24.105
Hey, how was it?

00:12:26.896 --> 00:12:28.355
Where's Detective Arashiyama?

00:12:28.855 --> 00:12:30.563
He said he had something to do.

00:12:30.646 --> 00:12:32.480
Keep an eye on him.

00:12:33.271 --> 00:12:35.771
I'm worried about that guy.

00:12:35.855 --> 00:12:36.688
Huh?

00:12:39.355 --> 00:12:42.230
He's going to be released soon.

00:13:01.980 --> 00:13:04.771
Why is Detective Arashiyama
still investigating this

00:13:04.855 --> 00:13:07.563
when the perpetrators have been arrested?

00:13:08.188 --> 00:13:09.855
He says it's baffling.

00:13:10.730 --> 00:13:12.105
What's baffling?

00:13:13.605 --> 00:13:14.813
Come here for a sec.

00:13:20.605 --> 00:13:23.855
There's no connection between
the turf where Inukai held influence

00:13:23.938 --> 00:13:27.771
and Detective Arashiyama's
daughter's house.

00:13:28.271 --> 00:13:30.480
It's not even a downtown area.

00:13:30.563 --> 00:13:32.396
They had no reason to go there.

00:13:33.396 --> 00:13:34.646
Inukai and his gang claim

00:13:34.730 --> 00:13:37.396
that they didn't know
Detective Arashiyama's daughter.

00:13:37.480 --> 00:13:41.230
So he suspects
that someone ordered them to do it.

00:13:42.688 --> 00:13:44.563
Was it Kengo Mibu?

00:13:44.646 --> 00:13:47.146
Or maybe those above him,
the Fushimi-gumi.

00:13:48.188 --> 00:13:51.438
Now, that's baffling in itself.
Why would he think that?

00:13:53.063 --> 00:13:55.396
He says it's his intuition as a detective.

00:13:55.480 --> 00:14:00.271
But the trial is over, and the sentence
has been finalized, so it's too late.

00:14:00.355 --> 00:14:05.605
And isn't Detective Arashiyama's
solo investigation a private one?

00:14:10.938 --> 00:14:13.938
Her phone, which was found
among her belongings, is locked.

00:14:14.021 --> 00:14:15.021
MIHO, MANAMI

00:14:15.105 --> 00:14:19.938
Nowadays, you can ask a professional
to analyze it for about 500,000.

00:14:20.438 --> 00:14:23.105
But back then, it wasn't possible.

00:14:24.313 --> 00:14:28.021
The investigation is over,
and the trial is over too,

00:14:28.105 --> 00:14:30.521
but nothing's over
for Detective Arashiyama.

00:14:34.063 --> 00:14:37.188
A six-digit passcode
has a million possible combinations.

00:14:37.271 --> 00:14:39.855
A few wrong attempts
and it won't respond for a day.

00:14:39.938 --> 00:14:43.855
That's left him in limbo for years,
day after day.

00:14:45.271 --> 00:14:49.188
The probability of unlocking it
is one in a million.

00:14:49.896 --> 00:14:51.980
He could just ask a professional.

00:14:54.355 --> 00:14:56.230
It's a parent's obsession.

00:14:57.313 --> 00:14:59.313
This abnormal behavior is the only way

00:14:59.396 --> 00:15:02.313
that he can stay connected
to his murdered daughter.

00:15:19.188 --> 00:15:20.730
It's a miracle.

00:15:23.063 --> 00:15:26.021
A miracle has happened
on Manami's death anniversary.

00:15:38.396 --> 00:15:40.730
FREQUENTLY USED ITEMS - HISTORY - CONTACTS

00:15:43.480 --> 00:15:46.355
CALL HISTORY
MIHO

00:15:48.313 --> 00:15:51.271
MIHO - MANAMI

00:15:54.188 --> 00:15:57.605
CALLING
MIHO

00:16:06.605 --> 00:16:09.605
Hello?

00:16:13.146 --> 00:16:16.063
I'm Manami Ogawa's father.

00:16:19.355 --> 00:16:22.730
Manami's… father?

00:16:24.896 --> 00:16:26.355
If you don't mind,

00:16:27.896 --> 00:16:30.688
could I ask you about my daughter?

00:16:49.771 --> 00:16:50.730
Um…

00:16:52.480 --> 00:16:55.438
Nice to meet you.
You're Miho Kinugasa, right?

00:16:55.521 --> 00:16:57.646
I'm Mr. Arashiyama.
I called the other day.

00:16:58.438 --> 00:16:59.271
Oh…

00:16:59.771 --> 00:17:01.355
Hello. I'm Ms. Kinugasa.

00:17:02.730 --> 00:17:03.730
Um…

00:17:05.396 --> 00:17:07.896
How did you know my daughter?

00:17:10.105 --> 00:17:12.396
We were like drinking buddies.

00:17:15.021 --> 00:17:17.521
Manami drank alcohol?

00:17:17.605 --> 00:17:19.355
Yes, quite a bit.

00:17:19.438 --> 00:17:21.855
Actually, a lot.

00:17:22.855 --> 00:17:26.480
We were kind of the pioneers
of getting paid to drink.

00:17:27.146 --> 00:17:32.688
We often drank together
in Nishiazabu and Roppongi.

00:17:32.771 --> 00:17:33.896
Paid drinking?

00:17:33.980 --> 00:17:36.146
With IT company CEOs and the like.

00:17:36.646 --> 00:17:42.480
We drank with guys who were living large.
We didn't know what they did for a living.

00:17:42.980 --> 00:17:46.188
And we got 30,000 for the taxi fare.

00:17:46.271 --> 00:17:49.355
30,000? Just for drinking?

00:17:49.438 --> 00:17:52.771
Well, as a single mother in her thirties,

00:17:52.855 --> 00:17:55.605
I don't belong there anymore.

00:17:57.355 --> 00:17:59.980
Your kid is crying. Is everything okay?

00:18:01.896 --> 00:18:06.396
It's fine. If I don't let the baby cry,
the nighttime crying will be worse.

00:18:07.230 --> 00:18:10.271
The person next door bangs on the wall.

00:18:17.438 --> 00:18:19.980
Ms. Kinugasa,

00:18:20.605 --> 00:18:24.521
can you give me
the contact information of those CEOs?

00:18:24.605 --> 00:18:27.855
I don't know their contact information.

00:18:30.105 --> 00:18:35.105
I was all about work and didn't know
anything about my daughter.

00:18:37.355 --> 00:18:40.646
But now, I want to know.

00:18:42.813 --> 00:18:45.896
Can you remember anything
that might be a clue?

00:18:50.105 --> 00:18:51.813
I wonder if it's still there…

00:18:52.813 --> 00:18:54.688
Manami's alt account.

00:18:55.188 --> 00:18:56.313
Alt account?

00:18:56.396 --> 00:18:58.688
Yeah. Her alternative account.

00:18:59.313 --> 00:19:00.188
Oh…

00:19:01.563 --> 00:19:02.563
Here it is.

00:19:02.646 --> 00:19:03.646
IMPOSSIBLE CAT

00:19:09.521 --> 00:19:12.271
Thank you for your cooperation.

00:19:16.271 --> 00:19:17.105
Um…

00:19:19.521 --> 00:19:21.980
I'm struggling
to make ends meet right now.

00:19:23.063 --> 00:19:25.730
I went out of my way
and made time to talk to you,

00:19:25.813 --> 00:19:27.896
so can you give me 30,000 yen?

00:19:31.813 --> 00:19:36.063
So you didn't do this out of kindness,
and now you want something in return?

00:19:37.396 --> 00:19:40.271
That's the side effect
of having earned money easily.

00:19:41.188 --> 00:19:43.896
Is that a good way to parent your child?

00:19:46.438 --> 00:19:49.605
Shut up.
That's a perfect example, old man.

00:19:50.813 --> 00:19:53.605
Your daughter hated you
because you're condescending

00:19:53.688 --> 00:19:55.605
and look down on everyone.

00:20:07.438 --> 00:20:11.396
IMPOSSIBLE CAT
0 FOLLOWING - 4 FOLLOWERS

00:20:12.521 --> 00:20:14.230
I want to be praised.

00:20:14.855 --> 00:20:17.605
Even if it's a lie, I want to be praised.

00:20:18.896 --> 00:20:21.480
Is this what they call
an attention seeker?

00:20:23.230 --> 00:20:25.396
I saw Koyashan's phone.

00:20:26.021 --> 00:20:30.313
There were pictures
of his beautiful wife and newborn baby.

00:20:31.355 --> 00:20:33.563
I was being deceived.

00:20:34.063 --> 00:20:35.480
An affair?

00:20:36.563 --> 00:20:41.188
Koyashan was once
the father of our child, you know?

00:20:47.521 --> 00:20:51.771
Dad's job is to punish bad people.

00:20:52.813 --> 00:20:56.396
He said, "If anything bad
happens to you, tell Dad."

00:20:57.980 --> 00:21:02.563
Dad was always at work,
and we hardly ever talked.

00:21:03.563 --> 00:21:08.188
My life was full of bad things happening,
but I couldn't say anything.

00:21:09.938 --> 00:21:12.980
I'm going to tell his wife
about our relationship.

00:21:13.480 --> 00:21:17.313
I'm going to tell my police officer dad
all of Koyashan's secrets.

00:21:17.396 --> 00:21:19.355
I'll drag him to hell with me.

00:21:22.230 --> 00:21:25.688
I plucked up the courage to call Dad.

00:21:26.271 --> 00:21:28.230
I wanted to ask him for advice.

00:21:29.688 --> 00:21:33.438
Is it okay to let jealousy
and anger take over?

00:21:34.063 --> 00:21:38.021
I don't want to stray from the right path.

00:21:38.105 --> 00:21:39.438
DAD

00:21:39.521 --> 00:21:41.980
Would Dad have guided me?

00:21:42.480 --> 00:21:44.771
MANAMI

00:21:51.063 --> 00:21:53.771
-What's wrong, Arashiyama?
-Oh, it's nothing.

00:21:53.855 --> 00:21:54.938
-Let's go.
-Yes.

00:21:55.021 --> 00:21:55.855
All right.

00:21:57.605 --> 00:22:00.438
I was busy with work,

00:22:01.688 --> 00:22:03.188
so I ignored the call.

00:22:03.980 --> 00:22:08.646
IMPOSSIBLE CAT:
BUT I COULDN'T TELL HIM

00:22:29.688 --> 00:22:30.938
Manami…

00:22:35.855 --> 00:22:40.105
MIHO - MANAMI

00:22:48.271 --> 00:22:50.480
Mr. Koyama, what is this place?

00:22:50.563 --> 00:22:51.688
Oh,

00:22:52.355 --> 00:22:54.605
this is a vacant room
that was for mistresses.

00:22:54.688 --> 00:22:56.313
You can use it if you like.

00:22:56.396 --> 00:22:59.396
Mr. Kyogoku offered it as a favor.

00:23:00.063 --> 00:23:02.605
CALLING
MR. KYOGOKU

00:23:05.438 --> 00:23:09.021
Oh, Attorney Kujo. It's Mr. Kyogoku.

00:23:12.230 --> 00:23:15.688
Please use Mr. Koyama's room.

00:23:15.771 --> 00:23:17.688
Why the sudden offer?

00:23:18.313 --> 00:23:19.771
I heard from Mibu.

00:23:19.855 --> 00:23:23.771
I'm worried about your health
because your living environment is so bad.

00:23:24.438 --> 00:23:26.188
No, thank you, Mr. Kyogoku.

00:23:26.688 --> 00:23:28.771
I'll find a house that suits me.

00:23:32.896 --> 00:23:35.146
Then, Attorney Kujo,

00:23:36.980 --> 00:23:39.188
how about being an advisor to Mr. Koyama?

00:23:40.646 --> 00:23:42.938
The CEO will pay you a lot.

00:23:43.605 --> 00:23:45.813
I value your skills.

00:23:46.396 --> 00:23:48.563
I'd love you to advise more companies.

00:23:48.646 --> 00:23:52.646
Well, they're all a little shady.

00:23:52.730 --> 00:23:56.396
I don't refuse requests based on
their status or if they're good or bad,

00:23:56.480 --> 00:23:58.188
but I won't become an advisor.

00:24:00.396 --> 00:24:01.563
What's the difference?

00:24:11.355 --> 00:24:13.021
Well, whatever.

00:24:14.021 --> 00:24:16.313
If you don't like the carrot,

00:24:16.896 --> 00:24:18.855
I'll hit you with the stick.

00:24:20.021 --> 00:24:20.938
One day…

00:24:22.938 --> 00:24:27.855
you will become
my obedient pigeon, Attorney Kujo.

00:24:46.605 --> 00:24:47.688
Hello.

00:24:48.438 --> 00:24:50.021
Attorney Karasuma.

00:24:50.855 --> 00:24:52.105
Where's Attorney Kujo?

00:24:52.188 --> 00:24:53.105
Well…

00:24:53.188 --> 00:24:54.230
You came alone?

00:24:54.313 --> 00:24:55.355
Yes.

00:24:56.646 --> 00:24:58.230
That's a first.

00:24:58.313 --> 00:24:59.438
What is it?

00:24:59.521 --> 00:25:02.605
Mibu, do you know Detective Arashiyama?

00:25:02.688 --> 00:25:04.813
The one from the Organized Crime Division.

00:25:05.646 --> 00:25:06.646
Kind of.

00:25:07.396 --> 00:25:09.521
What kind of detective is he?

00:25:11.605 --> 00:25:15.855
He's an annoying cop
who treats people like us like bugs.

00:25:16.563 --> 00:25:19.771
He'll drag you in for the smallest thing,
even if it's unrelated,

00:25:19.855 --> 00:25:21.688
and his interrogations are ruthless.

00:25:22.230 --> 00:25:25.646
But that's the right thing to do
as a detective, isn't it?

00:25:26.188 --> 00:25:28.730
Is it okay for an attorney
to say such a thing?

00:25:32.646 --> 00:25:33.771
Is that all?

00:25:35.730 --> 00:25:40.771
Tell me about the murder case
of Detective Arashiyama's daughter.

00:25:43.313 --> 00:25:45.646
You're acting like a detective.

00:25:45.730 --> 00:25:48.771
No, it's not
that I'm interested in the truth.

00:25:49.355 --> 00:25:53.480
I just want to know if you
or Mr. Kyogoku were involved.

00:25:53.563 --> 00:25:54.771
We were.

00:25:58.146 --> 00:25:59.730
What would you do if I meant it?

00:26:02.021 --> 00:26:04.230
Please stay away from Attorney Kujo.

00:26:11.646 --> 00:26:16.355
Detective Arashiyama will go to
any lengths to solve his daughter's case.

00:26:16.438 --> 00:26:19.646
He might make up a reason
to arrest Attorney Kujo.

00:26:20.605 --> 00:26:22.855
If, by any chance,
he was to be found guilty,

00:26:23.563 --> 00:26:26.688
he'd lose his attorney's badge,
and we'd both be finished.

00:26:26.771 --> 00:26:30.271
I won't let that happen.
I need Attorney Kujo too.

00:26:31.188 --> 00:26:33.105
I'll protect him no matter what.

00:26:40.605 --> 00:26:42.271
Then stay away from him.

00:26:45.438 --> 00:26:48.855
You guys just want to protect
Attorney Kujo for your own benefit.

00:26:48.938 --> 00:26:50.355
It's about money, right?

00:26:53.563 --> 00:26:55.146
But I'm different.

00:26:56.855 --> 00:27:00.355
No other lawyer is there for the weak
like Attorney Kujo.

00:27:02.396 --> 00:27:03.938
I want to protect that.

00:27:05.146 --> 00:27:07.480
Then who will protect us?

00:27:17.438 --> 00:27:18.938
You should be that person.

00:27:20.313 --> 00:27:22.605
A lawyer like Attorney Kujo.

00:27:23.105 --> 00:27:24.313
You should become one.

00:27:28.730 --> 00:27:29.813
Besides,

00:27:30.521 --> 00:27:32.938
whether he wants us
to stay away from him or not,

00:27:33.021 --> 00:27:34.980
shouldn't Attorney Kujo decide himself?

00:28:06.230 --> 00:28:08.438
ORGANIZED CRIME DIVISION

00:28:08.521 --> 00:28:10.271
Please wait here for a moment.

00:28:16.063 --> 00:28:17.188
Detective Arashiyama.

00:28:17.271 --> 00:28:18.105
Huh?

00:28:18.188 --> 00:28:19.855
A woman's here to speak with you.

00:28:26.146 --> 00:28:28.896
What? Did you remember something?

00:28:29.480 --> 00:28:33.646
Ms. Kinugasa, I can't pay you any money.

00:28:35.188 --> 00:28:37.063
Your kid's quiet today.

00:28:38.396 --> 00:28:40.188
After really thinking about it,

00:28:41.188 --> 00:28:42.563
Manami was the only one.

00:28:44.146 --> 00:28:46.396
Everyone else was indifferent.

00:28:47.021 --> 00:28:50.730
Manami was the only one
who really listened to my worries.

00:28:51.980 --> 00:28:53.355
I mean,

00:28:54.063 --> 00:28:57.813
everyone was trying
not to get entangled with me.

00:28:58.313 --> 00:29:01.188
Human relationships are a pain,
aren't they?

00:29:02.771 --> 00:29:05.313
If Manami was still alive,

00:29:05.813 --> 00:29:08.896
I think we could've stayed friends.

00:29:11.855 --> 00:29:14.355
So, what did you remember?

00:29:15.521 --> 00:29:16.855
Something about Koyashan.

00:29:18.271 --> 00:29:23.438
He was a pimp… or something like that.

00:29:24.646 --> 00:29:26.271
A pimp?

00:29:26.771 --> 00:29:32.438
He'd introduce unsuccessful bikini models
and underground idols

00:29:32.521 --> 00:29:35.521
to rich men for prostitution
and take a cut of the fee.

00:29:43.355 --> 00:29:45.355
He was dating Manami at the time.

00:29:48.021 --> 00:29:49.980
His name is Yoshiaki Koyama.

00:29:50.063 --> 00:29:52.355
YOSHIAKI KOYAMA

00:29:57.063 --> 00:29:59.688
Hey. I heard from Fukami.

00:30:00.313 --> 00:30:03.230
You're still looking into
your daughter's case.

00:30:04.938 --> 00:30:07.188
Well, I understand how you feel,

00:30:07.271 --> 00:30:09.688
but this case was solved ten years ago.

00:30:09.771 --> 00:30:12.063
You should focus on
what's in front of you.

00:30:19.271 --> 00:30:21.730
With all due respect, Captain Sumiyama,

00:30:21.813 --> 00:30:23.938
nothing has been solved.

00:30:25.063 --> 00:30:29.021
If you doubt whether what you're doing
is right, you can't put yourself at risk.

00:30:29.521 --> 00:30:33.355
We put our lives on the line for justice.

00:30:34.313 --> 00:30:38.938
Listen, Arashiyama.
Justice is decided by the organization.

00:30:39.438 --> 00:30:42.230
If you have a problem with that,
bring in more suspects.

00:30:43.605 --> 00:30:46.063
Stop investigating a case
from ten years ago.

00:30:47.188 --> 00:30:49.605
If you don't like it,
complain behind our backs,

00:30:50.480 --> 00:30:51.896
but hide your true feelings.

00:30:51.980 --> 00:30:54.396
Hey, Arashiyama.

00:30:55.730 --> 00:30:59.105
As expected of Attorney Kujo,
you got cut loose in 20 days.

00:30:59.188 --> 00:31:00.063
Yes.

00:31:00.146 --> 00:31:04.188
Oh, Mibu, thank you for arranging
for him to be my attorney.

00:31:04.271 --> 00:31:05.730
Was it tough staying silent?

00:31:05.813 --> 00:31:08.730
Yes. That damn Arashiyama was persistent.

00:31:09.480 --> 00:31:10.771
Arashiyama, huh?

00:31:11.938 --> 00:31:15.438
Oh, Inukai's getting out soon, right?

00:31:17.313 --> 00:31:18.146
Yeah.

00:31:27.771 --> 00:31:29.938
Please, Attorney Kujo.

00:31:30.021 --> 00:31:32.730
I can't forgive my ex-husband.

00:31:34.521 --> 00:31:35.730
Sachiko, calm down.

00:31:35.813 --> 00:31:38.605
First, could you tell me the details?

00:31:38.688 --> 00:31:39.730
I can't forgive him.

00:31:46.521 --> 00:31:48.146
Oh, I can't forgive him.

00:31:56.480 --> 00:31:58.605
Hello, this is Mr. Arashiyama.

00:31:58.688 --> 00:32:01.188
Ms. Kinugasa, is now a good time to talk?

00:32:01.271 --> 00:32:04.605
Oh, yes. But please make it quick.

00:32:06.771 --> 00:32:12.938
Could you tell me what "P5" and "P7"
in my daughter's messages mean?

00:32:13.021 --> 00:32:16.480
Those are the prices for prostitution.

00:32:16.563 --> 00:32:19.771
It means 50,000 yen
and 70,000 yen for sugar dating.

00:32:20.605 --> 00:32:23.855
Two hours for one means paid drinking.

00:32:25.146 --> 00:32:29.438
I didn't want to talk about it too much
because Koyashan's a little scary.

00:32:30.563 --> 00:32:32.438
But now that I'm a parent myself,

00:32:32.521 --> 00:32:36.646
I understand how you feel,
so I'll tell you something.

00:32:37.938 --> 00:32:38.896
Okay.

00:32:39.396 --> 00:32:41.980
He had many young mistresses.

00:32:42.063 --> 00:32:46.355
He threatened them
with drug-fueled sex and the yakuza

00:32:46.438 --> 00:32:48.855
and forced them into prostitution.

00:32:50.646 --> 00:32:53.271
Girls with daddy issues, you know…

00:32:53.355 --> 00:32:55.938
They've usually never
been praised by their parents.

00:32:56.021 --> 00:33:00.938
They feel they have no worth in life,
and they lose confidence in themselves.

00:33:01.688 --> 00:33:04.896
That's why they seek
romantic relationships,

00:33:04.980 --> 00:33:07.730
even if it means
having to accommodate the other person.

00:33:08.396 --> 00:33:12.938
Even though they're treated horribly,
they lie to themselves about reality.

00:33:16.313 --> 00:33:17.813
I'm like that too, though.

00:33:18.896 --> 00:33:20.980
Maybe Manami was also like that.

00:33:24.146 --> 00:33:25.771
I'm back.

00:33:35.646 --> 00:33:37.313
That's not true.

00:33:38.980 --> 00:33:39.980
Okay.

00:34:05.521 --> 00:34:07.521
Thank you, Attorney Karasuma.

00:34:30.771 --> 00:34:32.938
Hello, this is Kujo.

00:34:33.563 --> 00:34:36.313
Attorney Kujo, Koyama was arrested.

00:34:36.396 --> 00:34:37.855
Please do something.

00:37:16.521 --> 00:37:21.521
Subtitle translation by: Miho Kunisawa